						<div class="postbody">And what about scrooling like in <em>Sonic</em> games? The camera is not "attached" to the player, it tries to follow the player, but it moves on it's own. I played Sonic for years, but until this day I can not properly describe the behaviour of that camera. Wich means I'd probably have trouble implementing it in case I wished to.
<br />
<br />I really like the camera in Sonic. It tries to give you the best view of the surroundings, without beeing one of those annoying cameras that try to predict your actions. Like when you are facing left and right when you turn right the camera moves a lot to the right to show what's in front of you. That's a bit annoying.
<br />
<br />I never played paying much attention to that, though. Maybe if I spend some time with the game and keep the camera in mind, I might figure something out.</div>

